cat << 'EOF' > man_1_simple_shell
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "May 2026" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a basic UNIX command language interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.br
.B echo "command" | ./hsh
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a straightforward command-line interpreter. It reads commands from the standard input or a file and executes them. It was built as a core project for the Holberton School curriculum.
.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS
The following builtin commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit [status]
Exits the shell. If a status is provided, the shell exits with that integer status.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables to the standard output.
.TP
.B setenv [variable] [value]
Initializes a new environment variable, or modifies an existing one.
.TP
.B unsetenv [variable]
Removes an environment variable.
.SH AUTHORS
Written by Abeer Alsayari and Areej Alghamdi.
EOF

